# useCallback

`useCallback` returns a memoized version of the callback function that only changes if dependencies change. It's essentially `useMemo` for functions.

## Syntax

```jsx
const memoizedCallback = useCallback(() => {
  doSomething(a, b);
}, [a, b]);
```

## Why?

Functions are recreated on every render. If you pass a new function to a memoized child component, the child will re‑render (because the prop changed). `useCallback` keeps the same function reference between renders as long as dependencies don't change.

## Example

```jsx
function Parent({ id }) {
  const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
    console.log('Clicked', id);
  }, [id]);

  return <Child onClick={handleClick} />;
}

const Child = memo(({ onClick }) => {
  // Only re‑renders if onClick changes
});
```

